🖤I've never been a big fan of switching up workouts constantly. If you've trained with me for any length of time, chances are you repeat a lot of the same movements, but with different reps/weights.

Gym Mythbusters 👊🏼

✨️Muscle soreness is not an indicator of a good workout. Nor the lack of soreness an indicator of a poor one. 🫶🏼

✨️Sweat itself is not an indicator of workout performance. How much you sweat during movements depends on person to person!💦

✨️You don't have to dedicate 2 hours in the gym every day to reach your goals! A planned 30-45 minute intentional workout is plenty! Pick 4-5 movements and focus on form and time under tension!🔥

✨️For the love of everything holy ladies, lifting weights will not make you look like a beefy dude. 🙄 It would take extreme measures for your body to change in that manner. Lifting weights is EXACTLY what you should be doing to achieve that "toned" look you covet so much. 👌🏼

MIND TO MUSCLE ✨️

What does that even mean?? It means to bring mental attention to your body while you're working out. 💪🏼 

It's more than just lifting intentionally, though. You should be actively thinking about the targeted muscle while doing your movement. 🧐

For myself, triceps are incredibly difficult to target/develop. I have to keep reps nice & controlled and legit picture my tricep moving while I'm doing the movement. 😣

It takes some practice, but I promise it's worth it!! 😘

👎🏼No consistency.

You have to be committed to a regular workout. ✅️ I'm not saying you have to be in the gym 2 hrs a day, 6 days a week. But commit to a schedule 3-4x a week that will be maintainable for you!

👎🏼No mind to muscle connection. 🧠 
If you're coming into the gym with no plan and no concentration, you're not getting the most from your time. Mind to muscle zaps signals to our brains for those specific muscle fibers to contract, improving the quality of the movement= more gains.

👎🏼Not enough rest. 
Whether that's in between sets or sleep quality. When you exercise, you're creating little tears in your muscles 🥹💪🏼 During rest, these baby tears start to repair, ultimately resulting in stronger muscles. 

👎🏼You eat like an asshole. 😬
Nutrition is key & just as important as lifting weights. And if done properly, can catapult you to your goals. In the same breath, a shitty diet can hold you back from EVERYTHING. 

Bottom line, if you tell me you want to make changes, but all of this ⬆️ seems like "too much" for you, get out my face. ✋🏼

Hit me up when you're ready to make some real progress and giiirrrlll, I've GOT YOU.

Sunday mornings are a time of quiet reflection for me. 😌

I get up early just to have that time before the rest of the house starts waking up. Spending time this way gives me a sense of closure on the week behind me & gets me mentally prepared for the week ahead.

Some ways I spend my quiet time, in particular order:

✨️Water as soon as I wake
✨️Skin self care/iced-roller/gua sha
✨️Yoga/stretching/vacuums
✨️Devotional/mind-stilling/meditation 
✨️Reading/coffee 

Usually, I'm done by 830 or 9am and can start breakfast & get ready for church. ♡

Hope you're able to find time for yourself during the week. And if you don't, it might be time to start! 🤗

Happy Sunday!!

If you're anything like me, you will find yourself doing the same workouts every week because THAT'S where your gains are. 💪🏼 

But if the same routine is driving you 🥜, try this:

✨️Same move, slower rep✨️

Plan your workout routine with eccentric reps in mind. Take each rep & slow it down on the eccentric part of the movement for 3-4 seconds. Try & maintain the same number of reps. 😎

What are your fave Back workouts?! ⬇️

🍑Hip Thrusters🍑

Some tips to remember for the best booty gains:

✨️Use a full range of motion(booty down to the ground without touching & all the way back up. Push your hips to the ceiling & pause at the top).
✨️Push through your heels(think grinding your feet into the ground).
✨️Tuck that chin (find a spot to focus on about 6ft infront of you on the ground).
✨️Don't be afraid to pack on the weight. The full range of motion is shorter with a hip thruster, so it's easier to go heavier on this movement.
✨️As always, keep that core tight & breathe.
✨️Have fun with them & use different variations of thrusters!

Who would like to see some different thruster variations that I've used?! Let me know below.⬇️

✨️Mom Guilt✨️

💕It's a thing. And it can eat you alive. Especially if you don't have support on your journey. Or have outside opinions convincing you that the hour at the gym you spend each day is somehow damaging your children. 

You want my two cents? 

Fck that. 🖕🏼

Taking an hour for myself at 6am each day helps me be a better fckn human being. 💪🏼 My down days would be 100x worse if I didn't drag myself to the gym every morning. 🙃 I absolutely do not feel guilty when it comes to the gym time & here's why:

Some ways that lifting has helped me be a BETTER mother:

💕It's taught me patience.
💕Improves my sleep, which improves my attitude & 🧠 function.
💕Improves my mental health & lowers my anxiety.
💕Learning discipline & leading by example.
💕Shows my girls that they can be strong & beautiful at the same time.

These are just a few off the top of my head! The next time someone tells you you're being selfish for going to the gym (even if you DON'T have kiddos) politely tell them to eat a 🍆. 

Love you Queens! Now let's kick this Friday right in the 🍑.

*What even am I training rn? 😅*

MAMI! If your 🧠 is running 1,000 miles per hour 24/7, this one's for YOU! 🫡

So, you made it to the gym against all odds. ✅️ You have a workout plan ready.✅️ You've slept ok-ish, & had your H2O within that first hour of waking. ✅️ OMG, you're on a roll. 👏🏼 

You start your lift & your mind immediately starts rattling off random bs. 'Kids, work, bills, doc appointments, back to school prep, dinner plans, negative self-talk, your dashed dream of becoming a runway model, when is the last time you called your mom?' If you're anything like me, it's non-stop chatter up there. 📃 

But the gym is OUR TIME. 👸🏼The easiest way to quiet that noise is to FOCUS on what you're doing. Some days, I legit have to FORCE myself to picture the muscle I'm working in my mind and watching it move while I'm doing the exercise. By lifting with intent & enforcing mind-to-muscle connection, you can:

💕get the most out of your time
💕Improve your form & and avoid injuries 
💕Improve focus
💕increase muscle activation 
*And a favorite for me-
💕quiet my ever raging mind & allow me to de-stress 🙌🏼

So the next time you're at the gym & you start mentally making your grocery list or thinking about little Johnny's ortho appt time, I want you to remember this.

And STOP❣️

Our time for ourselves is limited, mommas! Make the most of it!! 😘

I get asked about lower body constantly! 🍑 You may be surprised by my answer when someone asks what I recommend to build a bigger booty:

Hamstrings.

Yes, I have a glute specific leg day & hip thrusters are a go-to, but incorporating a nice heavy hammie day has been a must for me! 🔥 

Not only is training hamstrings good for overall strength & stability, but by building the back of muscle, we help "lift" the glutes! 😏

Here are some of my fave hammie workouts. ⬇️

👽Deadlifts (bar or db)
👽RDLs (bar or db)
👽leg curls (I prefer lying)
👽Glute bridge variations
👽Bulgarian split squats 

Alright Queens, gimmie a 🦵🏽 if you're gonna focus on your hammies at least once this week! ⬇️

If you need some guidance, sign up for my online 1-1 booty program. 😘 Link in Bio.

Reasons it's awesome:
✨️increases hip mobility 
✨️increases hammie flexibility 
✨️strengthens core
✨️increases stability in the glutes & shoulders

While it's not inherently difficult, it does take quite a bit of concentration & control.
